# Playnite Plugin Standards

## Objective

- Produce production-ready, maintainable, and high-performance Playnite plugin code.
- Improve existing code quality when touching code (refactor, simplify, remove duplication).

## C# and plugin code (`.cs`)

When writing, editing, or reviewing **C#** (plugin logic, services, view models, non-XAML resources), follow **`.ai/Instructions & Rules.md`** end to end. It is the single source of truth for:

- Clarification policy, language (English for code and docs), and documentation expectations
- Naming conventions, C# 7.0 / .NET Framework 4.6.2 constraints, and dependency priority (`playnite-plugincommon` → Playnite SDK → BCL → NuGet with pros/cons)
- Playnite architecture, lifecycle, API usage (logging, serialization, localization keys usage from code, dialogs), and project-specific notes (`PluginExtended`, consistency section)
- Threading, asynchrony, performance, coding standards (clean code, braces, regions, async suffix, error handling), logging, and testing targets

**Before changing `.cs` files, open or @-mention `.ai/Instructions & Rules.md`** so its full guidance is in context.

## UI, XAML, and threading for views

- Follow **`.ai/Playnite UI Modernization, Localization and Common Styling.md`** for views, controls, styling, and localization structure.
- Localization keys and entries must be added or modified only in the appropriate `LocSource.xaml` scope (`source/playnite-plugincommon/CommonPluginsResources/Localization/Common` for shared strings, or `source/Localization` for plugin-specific strings).
- Do not add user-facing localized strings or localization keys in C# files, XAML views, or any other resource files outside the selected `LocSource.xaml`.
- Use dispatcher access for UI updates from background work.
- Never block UI thread with `.Result` or `.Wait()`; prefer `await`.

(Additional threading and async rules for all code also appear in **`.ai/Instructions & Rules.md`**.)

## Documentation and delivery (summary)

- Keep code, comments, XML docs, and README updates in English; document public APIs; no TODO placeholders.
- Full detail: **`.ai/Instructions & Rules.md`** (Language and Documentation, Response Rules, Out of Scope).
